    "body": "Problem: setting one underline style to false clears bits belonging to another style. `{underdouble = true, underdashed = false}` results in undercurl because CHECK_FLAG_WITH_KEY does `m &= ~flag` which doesn't work for multi-bit encoded values sharing HL_UNDERLINE_MASK.\r\n\r\nSolution: use a local variable to derive the correct clear mask from the flag. Clear the whole HL_UNDERLINE_MASK field instead of individual bits, and only clear on false when the current style actually matches.\r\n\r\nFix #38499\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-28T07:26:46Z",
    "comment_data": [],
